# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Apex Solutions — .gitignore
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Build output
bin/
obj/
[Bb]in/
[Oo]bj/
out/
publish/
artifacts/

# .NET / IDE user & cache files
*.user
*.suo
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates
.vs/
.idea/
*.DotSettings.user
project.lock.json
.vscode/*
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/launch.json
!.vscode/extensions.json

# Locally-installed .NET SDK (see README — SDK lives at ~/.dotnet, not committed)
.dotnet/
dotnet-install.sh
global.json.bak

# SQLite databases and their WAL/SHM/journal siblings.
# WARNING: git patterns like `*.sqlite` are slashless, so git matches them
# against EVERY path component — including directory names. A bare `*.sqlite`
# therefore ignores the entire `src/Apex.Persistence.Sqlite/` source tree
# (Schema.cs, SqliteCompanyStore.cs, Paisa.cs, .csproj), silently keeping the
# persistence project out of the repo. The runtime DB files use the `.db`
# extension (one .db per company), which `*.db`/`*.db-*` already cover, so the
# bare `*.sqlite` rule is dropped. The re-include below is a belt-and-braces
# guard: even if a `*.sqlite`-style rule is reintroduced, the source dir stays
# tracked. Actual `*.sqlite`/`*.sqlite3` DB files are still ignored elsewhere.
*.db
*.db-*
*.sqlite3
*.sqlite-*
# Never let a DB-file glob swallow the persistence source directory.
!src/Apex.Persistence.Sqlite/
!src/Apex.Persistence.Sqlite/**
# ...but keep build output and any DB files inside it ignored.
src/Apex.Persistence.Sqlite/bin/
src/Apex.Persistence.Sqlite/obj/
src/Apex.Persistence.Sqlite/**/*.db
src/Apex.Persistence.Sqlite/**/*.sqlite

# Rider / ReSharper
_ReSharper*/
*.[Rr]e[Ss]harper

# OS cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Logs & temp
*.log
*.tmp

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# THIRD-PARTY IP — NEVER COMMIT (CLAUDE.md R4). The entire tally/ folder holds
# copyrighted Tally Prime study PDFs and must stay out of the repository.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
tally/
